```

## **🤔 "Performances" Question:**

Currently **performances** are embedded in videos (`performance_date`, `venue`, `company`). If you want to index **unique performances** as distinct entities, you'd need:

```javascript
// Get unique performance contexts
const performances = await fetch('/api/videos/?fields=performance_date,venue,company').then(data => 
  // Frontend deduplicates to get unique performance events
);
```

## **🎯 Role-Specific Filtering:**

```javascript
// Just performers
const performers = await fetch('/api/people/?role=principal dancer');

// Just choreographers  
const choreographers = await fetch('/api/people/?role=choreographer');

// Browse by role
const roles = await fetch('/api/people/').then(data => 
  [...new Set(data.results.map(p => p.role))]
);
```

**So yes - you can index everything except "performances" as a separate entity.** If you need that, it's a simple addition, but the current video-centric model might be fine since each video = one performance context.

**Missing anything specific?**

**Perfect!** Now you have **first-class support** for all archive entities:

## **✅ New API Endpoints:**

```javascript
// All venues
const venues = await fetch('/api/venues/');

// All companies  
const companies = await fetch('/api/companies/');

// All performances (the key missing piece!)
const performances = await fetch('/api/performances/');

// All people (performers, choreographers, conductors, etc.)
const people = await fetch('/api/people/');

// All pieces
const pieces = await fetch('/api/pieces/');

// All videos (now linked to performances)
const videos = await fetch('/api/videos/');

// All clips
const clips = await fetch('/api/clips/');
```

## **🎭 Rich Relationships:**

**Performance** now includes:
- Venue details (capacity, location, type)
- Company info (artistic director, founding year)
- Cast information (who danced what role)
- Production details (conductor, stage director)
- Performance metadata (premiere, gala, matinee)

**Browse Patterns:**
```javascript
// All performances at Teatro Nacional
const performances = await fetch('/api/performances/?venue=1');

// All performances by Ballet Nacional in 2023
const performances = await fetch('/api/performances/?company=1&date__year=2023');

// All premieres
const premieres = await fetch('/api/performances/?is_premiere=true');

// All performances of Giselle across time
const gisellePerfomances = await fetch('/api/performances/?cast__piece=1');
```

**This gives you proper archival indexing:**
- Browse by venue → see all performances there
- Browse by company → see their history  
- Browse by piece → see all productions over time
- Browse by performer → see their career

**Much better for a dance archive!** Now you can build rich discovery interfaces around venues, companies, and the performance history of pieces. 🏛️✨

