**Perfect!** Now you have a **true archival system** that reflects reality:

## **🎯 What Changed:**

### **Videos = Digitized Containers**
- Source format (VHS, Betamax, 8mm, etc.)
- Condition assessment
- Provenance tracking ("found in basement")
- Estimated date ranges
- Donor information

### **Clips = Archival Intelligence**
- Performance identification (if known)
- Content type classification
- Confidence levels for identification
- Rich dance-specific metadata
- Verification workflow

### **Realistic Workflows:**
```javascript
// Find unidentified content needing review
const unknownClips = await fetch('/api/clips/unidentified/');

// Get all VHS tapes from the 1980s
const oldTapes = await fetch('/api/videos/?source_format=vhs&estimated_date_range=1980');

// Find clips that might be from Teatro Nacional
const teatroClips = await fetch('/api/clips/?performance__venue=1&identification_confidence=probable');
```

## **🎭 Archive Reality Example:**

```json
{
  "video": "VHS Tape #47 - Mixed 1980s Content",
  "clips": [
    {
      "title": "Giselle Mad Scene - Unknown Performer",
      "content_type": "performance", 
      "identification_confidence": "probable",
      "archival_notes": "Need to identify performer - check 1988 programs"
    },
    {
      "title": "Barre exercises", 
      "content_type": "class",
      "performance": null  // Not a performance!
    },
    {
      "title": "Swan Lake Variation - Different venue",
      "performance": "Teatro Real, 1989"  // Different performance!
    }
  ]
}
```

**This is exactly how real archives work!** One tape contains multiple unrelated segments, and the archival work happens at the clip level. Your CMS now supports the messy, wonderful reality of dance preservation! 🗄️✨

